On Sat, 7 Dec 2002, Snoopy wrote:

> What exactly would a deluxe be in a bay window?
>
> I always thought that the non campers had the chrome trim on the beltline

Just about every station wagon imported to the US was a Deluxe.  You are
right in that they had the aluminum trim along the beltline.  They also
have chrome emblems, metal strips in the window rubber, and a chrome
detail on the front air vent.

